SENATE CHAMBER
STATE OF OKLAHOMA DISPOSITION
FLOOR AMENDMENT No. ________
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
(Date)
I move to amend Senate Bill No. 640 as follows:
1. On Page 4, Line 15 and a half, by inserting a new paragraph 3 to read as follows:
“3. On and after the effective date of this act, if any place of worship is established within
three thousand (3,000) feet of any retail marijuana dispensary after a license has been issued by the
Authority for that location, the setback distance between properties shall not apply as long as the
licensed property is used for its original licensed purpose. The licensed location shall be
grandfathered in as to the setback distance as long as the property is used in accordance with the
original licensed purpose.”;
2. On Page 5, Line 10, by striking after the comma, the word “and”;
3. On Page 5, Line 20, by inserting after the word “issued”, and before the period, the following
language:
“, and
c. “place of worship” means any permanent building, structure, facility, or office space owned,
leased, or rented on a full-time basis, and used weekly for worship services, activities, or business of
the religious organization, which shall include, but not be limited to, churches, temples, synagogues,
and mosques” ; and
4. By amending the title to conform.
